               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-129-person1335">
                  SAMUEL 
                  BEAUMONT CHEESWRIGHT
               <interp inst="t18270913-129-person1335" type="surname" value="BEAUMONT CHEESWRIGHT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-129-person1335" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-129-person1335" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18270913-129-viclabel740" type="occupation">timber merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-129-victim1334 t18270913-129-viclabel740"></join>, and live in Kingsland-road - the prisoner was my <rs id="t18270913-129-deflabel741" type="occupation">sawyer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-129-defend1332 t18270913-129-deflabel741"></join>, and had no authority to take boards from my yard.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did not you authorize me to take out a plank that day? A. No; I left word for the carman to take it - but these are deals; the prisoner absconded next day - there was 5s. or 6s. due to him; when he was taken he said he took the deals out of the canal, but they were dry.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-129-person1336">
                  EBENEZA 
                  CHEESWRIGHT
               <interp inst="t18270913-129-person1336" type="surname" value="CHEESWRIGHT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-129-person1336" type="given" value="EBENEZA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-129-person1336" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 1st of August I saw the prisoner take a deal out of my father's yard, about eleven o'clock in the morning; and in the evening I saw him down the yard, tipsy, and in a few minutes he went down to the canal - I saw him afterwards with another deal on his shoulder; he had taken it through a place in the pales - I ran and told him to bring it back; he said he would not - for Mr. Barlow had told him to take it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-129-person1337">
                  MARY 
                  DOLTON
               <interp inst="t18270913-129-person1337" type="surname" value="DOLTON"></interp>
